cs.AR, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture): The paper proposes a hardware accelerator design for low-power, low-latency inference of fixed-point DNNs. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper uses the CIFAR-10 and ImageNet datasets to evaluate the performance of their proposed method, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper discusses the use of deep neural networks and their limitations, as well as proposes a novel approach to mapping floating-point DNNs to fixed-point DNNs. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper focuses on deep neural networks and proposes a method to reduce their computation overhead while maintaining accuracy. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a hardware/software co-design approach for implementing fixed-point DNNs on low-power, embedded platforms.
